Describe an event you attended in which you didn't like the music displayed
- what the event was
- where you were
- what the music was like
- explain why you did not enjoy the music

This topic reminds me of a birthday party I attended for one of my close friends about four years ago. He had just turned 20, which was quite a significant milestone, so he decided to celebrate it by hosting a party and inviting a group of friends, including me.

The party took place at a bar in District 1, although I can’t quite recall its name. It was actually a rock bar, as my friend was a huge fan of heavy metal music. At that time, I wasn’t familiar with that genre at all, and it was also my first time going to a bar, so I felt both curious and slightly nervous.

We went there on a Saturday night, and the place was absolutely packed, especially with foreigners. As soon as I walked in, I was overwhelmed by the loud atmosphere and the unique style of the crowd. Many people had long hair and wore dark clothing, which felt quite unusual to me at the time.

At first, everything was enjoyable. We arrived early, gave my friend our presents, took some photos, and spent time chatting while having a few drinks. However, things changed dramatically when a live metal band came on stage. The music was extremely loud and intense, with heavy electric guitar sounds and aggressive vocals that sounded more like shouting than singing. I could barely understand a single word.

What made it worse was that the performance went on for over two hours, and the volume was so overwhelming that it actually gave me a headache and made me feel quite dizzy. By the time I left, I felt exhausted and uncomfortable.

Overall, although I appreciated the experience, I didn’t enjoy the music at all because it was too loud and not to my taste. In fact, that was the last time I went to a rock bar like that.
